.SH NAME
retry \- run a command with automatic retries on failure
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]retry\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[B]\(en\f[R]] \f[I]command\f[R]
[\f[I]args\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs \f[I]command\f[R] and automatically retries it on failure.
Supports configurable retry count, delay, backoff strategy, jitter, and
exit\-code filtering.
.PP
A transparent wrapper \(em the child\(cqs stdout, stderr, and exit code
pass through unmodified on the final attempt.
Summary output goes to stderr by default, so it does not pollute piped
command output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R], \f[B]\(entimes\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Maximum number of retry attempts, not counting the initial run.
Default: 3.
.TP
\f[B]\-d\f[R] \f[I]D\f[R], \f[B]\(endelay\f[R] \f[I]D\f[R]
Delay before each retry.
Accepts a number followed by a unit suffix: \f[B]ms\f[R] (milliseconds),
\f[B]s\f[R] (seconds), \f[B]m\f[R] (minutes).
Default: \f[B]1s\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-b\f[R] \f[I]S\f[R], \f[B]\(enbackoff\f[R] \f[I]S\f[R]
Backoff strategy.
One of \f[B]fixed\f[R] (same delay every retry), \f[B]linear\f[R] (delay
increases by the base delay each retry), or \f[B]exp\f[R] (delay doubles
each retry).
Default: \f[B]fixed\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\(enjitter\f[R]
Add random jitter: the computed delay is multiplied by a random factor
between 0.5 and 1.0.
Useful when multiple processes may retry simultaneously.
.TP
\f[B]\(enon\f[R] \f[I]X\f[R][\f[B],\f[R]\&...]
Retry only when the exit code matches one of the given comma\-separated
values.
Any other exit code is passed through immediately without retrying.
.TP
\f[B]\(enuntil\f[R] \f[I]X\f[R][\f[B],\f[R]\&...]
Stop retrying when the exit code matches one of the given
comma\-separated values (poll mode).
Retries continue until the command exits with one of these codes or
attempts are exhausted.
.TP
\f[B]\(enstdout\f[R]
Write the summary to stdout instead of stderr.
.TP
\f[B]\(enjson\f[R]
Output results as JSON to stderr.
.TP
\f[B]\(encolor\f[R]
Force coloured output (overrides \f[B]NO_COLOR\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-color\f[R]
Disable coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enversion\f[R]
Show version.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R]
Show help.
.TP
\f[B]\(endescribe\f[R]
Emit machine\-readable JSON metadata (flags, examples, composability).
.SH EXIT CODES
